cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.RO 

This paper is likely to belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with visual tracking. The use of Bayesian formula and boosting techniques suggest that it may also belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The use of MILBoost approach and experiments with public datasets suggest that it may also belong to the Multimedia (cs.MM) and Robotics (cs.RO) sub-categories.
